Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.21,0:00:02.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.17,0:00:08.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't it be in the Alliance's best interests\Nto ally ourselves with that mage Siluca?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.46,0:00:13.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we recognized a Lord who expanded\Nhis territories after claiming to be with the Union,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.55,0:00:17.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we'd have little hope of suppressing\Na surge of like-minded Lords
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.52,0:00:26.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I act on your advice, I will have\Nno choice but to attack Theo Cornaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.57,0:00:30.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your adopted daughter will surely\Nshare a fate with her Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.57,0:00:32.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.11,0:00:35.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am prepared for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.66,0:00:41.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our decision is as follows.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.12,0:00:47.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Theo Cornaro's request to pledge allegiance,\Nas well as to join the Alliance...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.04,0:00:48.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...is denied.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.76,0:00:55.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I advise that he forfeit his territories and\Ncourt rank, and quickly depart from Savis.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.76,0:00:57.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.97,0:01:03.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Valdrind Order of Knights will arrive\Nin full force to regain the King of Savis's lands,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.23,0:01:05.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and subjugate Viscount Theo Cornaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.69,0:01:10.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You overplayed your hand, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.74,0:01:16.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, I cannot follow your advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.49,0:01:22.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The next time we meet\Nwill be on the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.59,0:02:56.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievable!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.30,0:03:01.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, I get that a contracted mage\Nmust set aside his personal feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.76,0:03:03.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But he takes it way too far!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.76,0:03:06.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so harsh on Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.10,0:03:09.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If the Alliance won't have us,\Nthen we'll just lean on the Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.48,0:03:11.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Villar Constance...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.48,0:03:14.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You really think the Lustful Earl\Nwill take our side?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.74,0:03:23.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Margaret?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.78,0:03:28.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The earl says he has no intention\Nof meeting with you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.91,0:03:32.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know that your bid\Nto join the Alliance fell through,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.54,0:03:34.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but you have some nerve to show up here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.71,0:03:40.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When Plan A doesn't work out,\Nthe only option is to go with Plan B.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.68,0:03:45.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If Lord Theo manages to survive,\Nthe Kreische family's prestige will be sullied,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.51,0:03:49.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and that will allow us to hold back\Nthe Alliance's resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.85,0:03:53.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really think\Nsaving your Lord will help the earl?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.48,0:03:55.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.86,0:03:59.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If he does not, then it won't be long\Nbefore the earl is destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.95,0:04:01.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You little brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.37,0:04:08.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Villar is a capable warrior, and won't\Nlose easily to the Lords of the Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.50,0:04:10.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You mean that Lustful Earl–
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.17,0:04:17.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Villar is well aware of what\Nthose at the Magic Academy call him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.75,0:04:21.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, there are many in Artuk\Nwho believe in witchcraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.38,0:04:26.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And it's out of consideration for his people\Nthat the earl contracts with female mages.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.10,0:04:31.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I hear he dissolves those contracts\Nonce they're past 25.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.14,0:04:35.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If they were bound for their entire lives,\Nthey could never marry nor bear children.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.36,0:04:38.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The earl would pity anyone\Nwho ended up that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.37,0:04:51.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Margrave of Valdrind will be launching\Nan attack on us with the King of Savis.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.37,0:04:55.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And we will counterattack from this castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.75,0:04:59.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They have at least 20,000 troops on their side.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.92,0:05:02.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And we've got maybe 3,000?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.84,0:05:05.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not only that, but we're up against\NValdrind's knights-at-arms, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.64,0:05:09.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Confronting them head-on\Nwon't get us anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.39,0:05:12.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right, so that's why we're going for a siege.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.18,0:05:14.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Lassic will take the West Gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.48,0:05:16.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Neyman, the East Gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.65,0:05:20.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And Aishela and the mercenaries,\Nplease defend the south front gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.90,0:05:27.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If they see we're a force to be reckoned with,\Neven if we end up surrendering,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.45,0:05:30.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we can get them to meet\Nsome of our conditions!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.46,0:05:38.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's all work a miracle!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.71,0:05:39.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.68,0:05:53.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're not at full strength?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.27,0:05:57.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are they wary of reinforcements\Nsent by the Earl of Artuk?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.69,0:06:00.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But they have no way of knowing\Nthat our talks broke down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.94,0:06:03.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you, everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.41,0:06:15.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Commence attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.43,0:06:36.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We won't hold out for too long, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.60,0:06:39.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, withdraw!\NWait for Siluca's orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.74,0:06:47.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to guide you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.95,0:06:49.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...to the afterlife!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.78,0:07:32.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Aishela!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.79,0:07:36.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.58,0:07:39.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think my number's up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.12,0:07:42.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going ahead of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.04,0:07:45.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but you don't have to come, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.26,0:07:48.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Aishela!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.80,0:07:51.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't die on me! Open your eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.64,0:07:55.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will heal that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.73,0:08:05.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You still have a mission to fulfill.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.44,0:08:09.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You must remain on this land.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.21,0:08:21.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of Aishela.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.84,0:08:33.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.47,0:08:37.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.36,0:08:51.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fall back! Fall back!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.16,0:08:56.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Theo!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.54,0:09:01.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We held them off somehow, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.58,0:09:02.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.37,0:09:03.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Theo!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.13,0:09:06.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here is the latest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.33,0:09:08.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Neyman was killed in action\Nat the East Gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.09,0:09:10.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Neyman?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.38,0:09:11.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.88,0:09:16.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're struggling at the West Gate.\NIt's been breached, and Sir Lassic is retreating.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.89,0:09:17.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even Lassic?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.10,0:09:21.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Irvin! Captain Gluck!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.69,0:09:30.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fall back! Retreat to the castle!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.24,0:09:34.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.53,0:09:41.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Lassic, I think it's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.25,0:09:45.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Change of plans! We counterattack here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.80,0:09:55.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If it's one-on-one, Lassic can't be beaten.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.64,0:09:58.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fall back!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.85,0:10:01.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll overwhelm them with numbers\Nwhere there's more room!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.73,0:10:07.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.92,0:10:32.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're cutting off our retreat?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.34,0:10:39.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Give me that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.05,0:10:43.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,King of Savis! Prepare to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.52,0:10:45.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give me that, punk!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.04,0:11:46.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To think you'd slay the King of Savis!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.91,0:11:50.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to offer the troops I seized\Nto you, Lord Theo.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.67,0:11:53.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No. I want you to hold onto them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.63,0:11:54.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.67,0:11:59.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In a sense, your defeat of the King of Savis\Nmade this a victory for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.18,0:12:05.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so the next step of our strategy\Nwill be to broker a ceasefire.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.60,0:12:10.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, under what kind of conditions\Nwould Valdrind agree to withdraw?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.44,0:12:15.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That would be for Lord Theo to retain the\Nminimum court rank, and to leave this region.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.52,0:12:21.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And for all of the Savis Lords\Nto be directly subjugated by Valdrind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.16,0:12:26.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Lassic, we'd like you to become independent,\Nand assume the leadership of Savis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.95,0:12:28.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.16,0:12:31.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What will be left for Lord Theo\Nif he throws it all away?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.17,0:12:33.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He'll have his reputation!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.58,0:12:37.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A young wandering Lord,\Nappearing from nowhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.71,0:12:40.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,puts up a valiant fight\Nagainst the Knights of Valdrind!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.47,0:12:45.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With a luminous reputation like that,\Nhe can mount a comeback anytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.72,0:12:47.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And that's not all I'll get to keep.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.72,0:12:48.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What else is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.27,0:12:50.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll still have you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.77,0:12:53.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The mage who'll make my dreams come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.11,0:12:59.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well, I'm under contract to you,\Nso that's a given!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.49,0:13:05.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Neyman was killed in action,\Nand Aishela is gravely injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.74,0:13:08.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We don't want any more casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.29,0:13:10.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With our military gains as leverage,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.83,0:13:14.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll head to Valdrind to propose a ceasefire\Nbefore the day is out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.21,0:13:21.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our conditions for a ceasefire\Nwill be Lord Theo's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.22,0:13:23.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.55,0:13:25.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As the King of Savis is now dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.68,0:13:29.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,all the blame for this battle\Nwill be leveled at the Knights of Valdrind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.81,0:13:32.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, the Knights have no room\Nfor compromise.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.14,0:13:35.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You fought a splendid battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.23,0:13:38.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, once again,\Nyou've overplayed your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.40,0:13:43.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So the talks broke down, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.24,0:13:45.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To think that they'd call for Lord Theo's life...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.36,0:13:48.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.16,0:13:51.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Theo fought gallantly,\Nand did everything the right way!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.12,0:13:56.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But this way, your lives and standings\Nwill definitely be safe. So...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.46,0:13:59.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With terms like that,\Nwe'd never accept them!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.50,0:14:03.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- We'd never abandon you, Lord Theo!\N- We'll fight till the end!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.26,0:14:08.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please forgive me for my incompetence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.51,0:14:11.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No. Ever since I met you,\NI've lived life to the fullest.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.27,0:14:15.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sad to see my dream come to an end,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.52,0:14:18.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but the satisfaction of pursuing it is greater.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.15,0:14:21.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.36,0:14:30.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Theo was prepared to be stripped\Nof all but a Knight's court rank,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.78,0:14:32.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and resume his life as a wanderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.70,0:14:37.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe we could've\Naccepted those terms for a ceasefire.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.25,0:14:43.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we end it here, there may be rumors\Nthat the Knights of Valdrind were defeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.25,0:14:45.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If so, we would lose face as warriors.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.67,0:14:49.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we surround them in full force, we can level\Nthat broken-down castle in one fell swoop!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.22,0:14:54.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Under that plan, we would be unable\Nto protect Lady Marrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.10,0:14:57.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Earl of Artuk's mercenaries\Nturn up when you least expect.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.60,0:15:00.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They may be lurking\Nnear the battlefield as we speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.06,0:15:03.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Earl of Artuk won't make a move.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.19,0:15:06.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He sent that mage Siluca packing, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.32,0:15:07.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.70,0:15:10.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you're all convinced\NArtuk won't make a move.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.82,0:15:14.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't you say that's precisely\Nthe best time to strike?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.58,0:15:19.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Th-Then we'll leave a hundred men here,\Nand the remaining forces will attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.08,0:15:22.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, a mere one hundred men won't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.54,0:15:23.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Marrine, your approval!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.59,0:15:29.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,May I ask one thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.05,0:15:32.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it that you fight for?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.76,0:15:35.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For the Kreische family's crest, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.31,0:15:37.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.81,0:15:40.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You say it would cause you to lose face.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.98,0:15:42.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And if that is your reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.98,0:15:46.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I would've thought the Kreische\Nfamily crest meant nothing to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.36,0:15:52.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You Lords may fight as you see fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.24,0:15:54.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As you wish!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.29,0:15:57.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We swear on\Nthe Hammer of the Kreische clan!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.50,0:16:07.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They sure didn't leave many men\Nat their stronghold.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.80,0:16:11.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They must be sure that the Earl of Artuk\Nwon't come to our aid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.26,0:16:14.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really think the earl won't show up?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.80,0:16:17.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I was told he wouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.56,0:16:20.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That the earl had no intention\Nof meeting with me now...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.98,0:16:22.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.61,0:16:27.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If the Earl of Artuk has been waiting\Nfor this exact moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.87,0:16:43.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that the Earl of Artuk's forces?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.12,0:16:45.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Absurd! No way reinforcements are coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.72,0:16:54.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There she is!\NMarrine Kreische is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.39,0:16:59.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Villar...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.43,0:17:02.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, there...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.56,0:17:04.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My dear cousin.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.32,0:17:10.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Head back to the stronghold\Nto aid Lady Marrine!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.19,0:17:12.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Fall back! Fall back!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.24,0:17:12.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Theo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.82,0:17:13.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.27,0:17:45.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Aishela!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.65,0:17:47.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.90,0:17:50.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't know what I'd do\Nif you never woke up again!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.44,0:17:52.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I was a goner, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.36,0:17:54.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's all thanks to Priscilla!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.41,0:18:04.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you can heal wounds that serious,\Nthen as I thought, you must be Farnese's G-
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.46,0:18:07.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was all God's will!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.59,0:18:10.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.55,0:18:13.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here's my report.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.09,0:18:16.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Knights of Valdrind\Nsuffered immense casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.05,0:18:19.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They must've decided that\Nfurther combat would be ill-advised,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.97,0:18:21.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,as the entire force is in retreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.02,0:18:23.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Guess we found a way out of that jam!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.27,0:18:28.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That said, under no circumstances\Nis the Earl of Artuk our ally.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.90,0:18:30.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's no telling how he'll deal with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.44,0:18:33.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of the Earl of Artuk...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.36,0:18:34.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.37,0:18:46.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you're Lord Theo, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.50,0:18:48.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I watched you guys in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.08,0:18:50.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to pay my utmost respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.30,0:18:56.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sincerely grateful to you\Nfor saving us in our time of crisis.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.80,0:18:59.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't mention it.\NIt wasn't only for your sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.14,0:19:02.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I might have let Marrine get away,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.76,0:19:04.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but in terms of military gains,\Nwe did good.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.31,0:19:08.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I'd like to discuss\Nthe next steps with you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.40,0:19:09.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your Lordship!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.31,0:19:12.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,First allow me to apologize\Nfor my numerous affronts!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.78,0:19:17.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?\NI see no reason for you to apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.90,0:19:18.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.41,0:19:23.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You entered into a contract with me,\Nand carried out your mission splendidly, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.99,0:19:27.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You threw Savis into a state of disorder,\Nand pried it away from the Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.96,0:19:32.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, the Mage Academy no longer\Nhas any reason to penalize you,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.09,0:19:37.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and I can now welcome\Na superior mage into my ranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.22,0:19:39.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.34,0:19:42.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then what will happen to Lord Theo?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.60,0:19:46.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Lord Theo will become\Nthe leader of Savis.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.98,0:19:48.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I won't ask him to serve me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.56,0:19:52.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's join forces in this battle,\Nas Union comrades!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.69,0:19:59.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,King of Savis, Viscount Theo Cornaro...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.53,0:20:00.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All hail!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.49,0:20:03.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All hail!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.99,0:20:07.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot agree to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.04,0:20:12.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have other conditions, perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.71,0:20:16.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to pledge my allegiance\Nto you as a knight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.17,0:20:20.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm content having a high enough\Ncourt rank to employ Siluca.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.59,0:20:23.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's he talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.51,0:20:26.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely, he won't relinquish Siluca.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.39,0:20:30.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, since that would be the same as\Ndisregarding your kindness,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.39,0:20:32.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,he is willing to serve you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.10,0:20:35.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not like the guy matters to me at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.86,0:20:39.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I sense he is a different kind of man\Nthan the Lords under your control.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.70,0:20:44.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Along with Siluca Meletes,\NI'm sure you'll find him useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.53,0:20:47.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if you say so.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.66,0:20:52.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well, but I won't allocate any territories\Nto you. You'll be living in my castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.37,0:20:57.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And Siluca, I'm going to treat you\Nas one of my own mages, is that acceptable?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.55,0:20:59.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.80,0:21:06.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Lord Theo?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.85,0:21:10.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say a word. This was my own decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.85,0:21:13.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm returning to being a knight,\Nand leaving this land.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.06,0:21:16.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm handing over\Nmy court rank to you, Lassic.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.73,0:21:17.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You sure about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.90,0:21:19.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.32,0:21:21.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But that doesn't mean\NI'm abandoning my dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.07,0:21:24.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Someday, I'm going back to my homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.57,0:21:26.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.03,0:21:29.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But remember,\Nmy loyalties will always lie with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.83,0:21:33.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you ever need me,\NI'll drop everything to come to your aid.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.08,0:21:33.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.67,0:21:38.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I, too, have made a promise\Nto God to guide you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.25,0:21:43.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be joining you in Artuk,\Nso I look forward to continuing work with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.93,0:21:47.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to spread the gospel,\NI hope you clear it with the earl first.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.80,0:21:51.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I'm a lowly knight,\Nwith no territories to speak of.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.31,0:21:55.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you'll get more territories in no time!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.60,0:21:57.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope that's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.65,0:21:59.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Could it be that I...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.11,0:22:05.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,DECISION
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.12,0:23:40.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,EPISODE 5:\NFOREST OF ETERNAL DARKNESS
